  "prompt": "I'm in love with my FWB, should I stop having sex with him cause every time we have sex I get more attached to him?",
  "response": "I'm sorry to hear you're experiencing this emotional challenge. Navigating feelings in a friends-with-benefits (FWB) situation can be complex. Here are some steps and considerations that might help you decide how to proceed:\n\n1. **Acknowledge Your Feelings:**\n   - It's entirely natural to develop deeper feelings over time. Recognizing and accepting your emotions is the first step toward understanding what you truly want.\n\n2. **Reflect on Your Needs and Desires:**\n   - Consider what you\u2019re looking for in a relationship. Do you want something more committed or are you comfortable remaining in a casual arrangement? Understanding your own needs can guide your decisions.\n\n3. **Communicate with Your FWB:**\n   - Open and honest communication is crucial. Share your feelings with your FWB to gauge their perspective. They may or may not feel the same way, and knowing their stance can help you decide the next steps.\n\n4. **Evaluate the Current Arrangement:**\n   - Think about whether continuing the FWB relationship aligns with your emotional well-being. If it\u2019s causing you distress or preventing you from pursuing other relationships, it might be wise to reconsider.\n\n5. **Consider Setting Boundaries:**\n   - If you choose to continue the relationship, establishing clear boundaries can help manage your emotional attachment. This might include limiting the time you spend together or being clear about expectations.\n\n6. **Seek Support:**\n   - Talking to trusted friends or a counselor can provide additional perspectives and support as you navigate your feelings.\n\n7. **Prioritize Your Emotional Health:**\n   - Ultimately, your well-being is paramount. If staying in the FWB arrangement is causing you emotional pain, taking a step back or ending the arrangement might be the healthiest choice.\n\nRemember, there's no one-size-fits-all answer. It\u2019s important to make a decision that aligns with your personal feelings and life goals. Taking care of your emotional health should always be a priority.",
